For eureka client (all 3 microservices)
in current application.properties the properties specified
eureka.client.register-with-eureka = true
eureka.client.fetch-registry = true
eureka.client.serviceUrl.defaultZone=http://localhost:8761/eureka/
are optional and currently filled as it is it's default value so we can ommit defining above 3 properties for all as all are filled with default properties only

servicereg should be started first and then all 3 microservices should started not doing so will result into
error such as not able to find eureka server etc.. 

after successfull registration on the dashboard of eureka server(localhost:8761) we will see all the instances registered with eureka server
"Instances currently registered with Eureka"
